Text: Phew... I'm beat...
I'm not tired at all!

You're so weak, Eta, if just pressing a switch makes
you tired!
Okay, okay...

Mr. Vendy emits puffs of smoke and has completely
stopped functioning.
Hey, branch manager. We're done here, soâ€”

Delta turns towards where the branch manager is,
when...
Whoaaaaa!!! You ladies are amaaazing!!!

A wave of applause and cheers erupts from the crowd
evacuated by the Mitsugoshi branch's employees.
Wh-What the heck it this?!
No idea...
That was awesome, witch lady! You're super strong!
Thanks for protecting us! You looked really cool!

Mom! The witch lady and the vampire lady defeated the
bad Mr. Vendy!

Yes, that was incredible. I'm surprised by how much
of a show they put on.

Mitsugoshi always manages to impress. I can't believe
Mr. Vendy was part of this performance all along!
Performance...?
...The misunderstandings are escalating...

I thought you were weirdos giving out sweets...but
you're actually pretty amazing!
Thanks for getting our sweets back!
Witch lady, vampire lady, can I shake your hands?!
H-H-Hey... No pushing!
E-Eta! What's going on?!

...Don't know. There are a lot of people...
Wanna run?

No...running! I'm not sure, but I feel...nervous?
Excited? How about you, Eta?
Well...I don't feel bad...

Yup, yup. It's really something that they get how
awesome I am.

Eta and Delta find themselves surrounded by children
who gaze at them as if they are heroes.
Hey, witch lady! Trick or treat!
Hmm?
Me too! Miss Vampire! Trick or treat!
...Huh?

Hehehe. Witch lady and vampire lady, would you please
give out sweets to the children?

The two exchange glances as the branch manager smiles
and makes this request. Then...
Heehee! Well, since you insist, I'll do it!
...Oh well...
Okay, kids! Say the magic words!

Trick or treat! Give us candy, or we'll play tricks
on you!
Trick or treat!
Here you go...
Thank you, miss!
...Mm. You're welcome.

It's only after Eta and Delta finish handing out
sweets to the children that they realize they
both have smiles on their faces.
Lady Eta, Lady Delta, well done!

Despite the unfortunate trouble that occurred,
thanks to both of you, it didn't escalate into
a major incident. In fact, the Halloween event
was a great
success!

After giving out all the sweets, Eta and Delta return
to the Mitsugoshi branch.

Heehee! It's a piece of cake when I get serious
about it!

...Kids have way too much energy...but...well,
it wasn't not fun...

Umm... It wasn't not fun... Hmmm...oh! Which means it
was fun!

I had fun too! I think I sorta got what you were
saying!
Huh?
...That thing you said about customer service.

Ah... I'm really glad you were able to gain some
understanding of our philosophy at Mitsugoshi.
Thank you very much.
Halloween was such a great festival!

...Yeah. I'll prepare a more perfect Mr. Vendy for
next year...

With their work completed, satisfied smiles adorn the
faces of the witch and vampire.

That concludes the report submitted by the branch
manager regarding Eta and Delta's assistance at the
Mitsugoshi branch.

I was worried about how things would turn out,
but those girls really gave it their all.

Within the private office of the Shadow Garden,
Alpha listens to Gamma's report and nods with
a satisfied expression.

...Yes. We have successfully completed the training
for the new recruits. Eta and Delta are expected to
return tomorrow.

Then what's with the long face? I saw that same
expression on you just the other day.

...Please take a look at this. It's the report and
the balance sheet.
Let me see.

Here. Sales at Mitsugoshi's main store have been
strong this year, thanks to the events held in
various locations. The Halloween sales campaign
was a big success. However...
This is...a serious issue.

Alpha groans upon seeing the balance sheet, and
Gamma's expression is tinged with gloom...

The next day, after returning from the Mitsugoshi
branch, Eta and Delta visit Alpha's office to deliver
their report...
We're back! I did a perfect job!

...I've done a year's worth of work... I'll be holed
up in my research lab for a while...
We deserve to be rewarded...for ourâ€”
Eep?!
...I'm getting chills!

The two enter the office in high spirits, but they
come to an abrupt stop.

Welcome back. It seems you two had quite the
Halloween.
Wh-Why're you so angry?!
Take a look at this.
...The balance sheet...?

The Halloween sales campaign was a success, and sales
are up...but there's one problem. Take a look at the
expenses on the balance sheet.
Expenses?
Expenses...right...

Delta, these expenses on Mitsugoshi's tab are from
you, aren't they?

Mitsugoshi's tab! If you say those magic words at the
food stalls, you can get food without paying!

It's not "without paying." It means they trust
Mitsugoshi enough to postpone payment. 
And as for you, Eta...
...Mr. Vendy, huh...?

So, you're aware of it. How reassuring. What's the
deal with the massive production costs? They're
enough to offset the sales from the branch you
visited.
...But they were necessary expenses...

If I knew what "Mitsugoshi's tab" meant, I wouldn't
have done it! So...it's all the fault of the food stalls!

Sounds like you're making excuses... I wonder if
you're truly reflecting on your actions...
Eep?! Y-Yes, I am...
I shouldn't have come here...

And so, Eta and Delta's Halloween comes to a close
amidst Alpha's thunderous rage...
